entor-size-]>a{color:inherit;font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit}.elementor-widget-heading .elementor-heading-title.elementor-size-small{font-size:15px}.elementor-widget-heading .elementor-heading-title.elementor-size-medium{font-size:19px}.elementor-widget-heading .elementor-heading-title.elementor-size-large{font-size:29px}.elementor-widget-heading .elementor-heading-title.elementor-size-xl{font-size:39px}.elementor-widget-heading .elementor-heading-title.elementor-size-xxl{font-size:59px}<\/style><h5 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">About Us<\/h5>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-fe8a4b3 elementor-widget thim-ekits-heading elementor-widget-thim-heading\" data-id=\"fe8a4b3\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"thim-heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"sc_heading \"><h3 class=\"title\"><\/h3><div class=\"sub-heading\"><p>Little Angels British Schools Aguleri is a vision and mandate given to His Lordship, the Rt.Rev. Dr Paul Amechi Udogu, the 1st Aguleri Indigenous Bishop and the Lord Bishop of Afikpo Diocese.<br \/>\n His Lordship Dr Paul A Udogu is an Educationist and a Spiritual leader having studied in the following institutions of higher learning: St Francis of Assisi Theological College Wusasa Zaria, Ahmed Bello University Zaria, Kaduna State, University of Jos, Jos Plateau State, Theological College of Northern Nigeria Bukuru Jos, Nnamdi Azikiwe University Awka, Canterbury Cathedral college and Anglican Leadership Center in Rome and obtained the following certificates: Dip. Theo, Dip C.R.Ed, B.D, B.A, MA, PhD. His Wife Hon Mrs Blessing Chinwendu Udogu who is the head of Administration of the school is a trained Teacher and Educationist with many years of experience. She holds an NCE, B.Ed. and M.Ed. in Guidance and Counseling.<\/p>\n<p>Little Angels British Schools Aguleri which is co-educational runs Cr\u00e8che, Nursery, Primary and Secondary Schools. It is located at Eziagulu Aguleri near Aguleri Junction. Our Vision is to raise responsible Children who will be God-fearing, sound in morality and Academics and who are equipped to compete with their mates in any parts of  the world. The school resumed on september,  for 2023\/2024 Academic session. The school provides a positive environment which the pupils\/students, teachers & parents interact in the teaching and learning process.<br \/>\nThe programs in the school are highly learner-focused with the aim of offering an education that affects the head, the heart and the hands positively. A major development of all the school's facilities is ongoing, making the school facilities the best among the most modern in Nigeria and Anambra State in particular. The development is strongly focused on enhancing the teaching\/learning environment of the school. Specialized programs for all students in computing and information technology, entrepreneurship, library and physical education are provided.<\/p>\n<p>The school is a designated lighthouse school for gifted education programs, providing a whole school approach, the horizon program for students of all ages. Students with particular learning needs and indigenous support activities are an integral part of the school's program. Opportunities are available for students to participate in a wide range of curriculum extension activities, including band and instrumental instruction, student leadership and governance programs, sporting, social, agriculture, skill acquisition and community caring programs.<\/p>\n<p>Hence our school is positioned to be a centre for academic excellence with the mission of providing adequate opportunity and Christian training to all students and pupils to enable them to excel in all areas of life. <\/p>\n<p>To enhance the attainment of this vision, we provided adequate modern teaching and learning ICT facilities with highly skilled and qualified teachers.<\/p>\n